Package us.mattgreen

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Talkable
    Interface that allows for the person, and pet classes to implement speech into their classes.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Cat
    This class creates a Cat by extending the pet class and allows it to talk by implementing the Talkable interface.
    Dog
    This class creates a Dog by extending the pet class and allows it to talk by implementing the Talkable interface.
    FileInput
    File input is to read a file, it is not being used as of now.
    FileOutput
    This class is is used for writing person, and pet classes to a text file.
    Main
    Creates several objects of different types of animals, writes them to the console, and writes them to a file called animals.txt
    Person
    This abstract class defines what any children of the Person class must have.
    Pet
    This abstract class creates different animal style objects that can be pets.
    Student
    This child class extends the Person class to create objects that represent a student.
